As we progress through summer, we wanted to share a couple of resources that we have available right in our community to help feed families now that school is out.

Saltbox Ministries and Bountiful Gifts have been providing hot meals and bags of groceries 2 Sundays or more of every month. These hot meals are provided for ANYONE who is willing to come to the SALTBOX building between 4-6 pm on the scheduled days. Each car that comes through has also been provided with a number of grocery items to help keep families fed even after the hot meal has been eaten. These hot meals and groceries are delivered right to each car, allowing for safety.

Items provided vary but have often included milk,…

post_text:
You may have seen or heard that Northwest Local Schools were approved for blended learning, which includes remote learning. At this point in time, we do not have clarity from the health department, Ohio Department of Education and government regarding next year. However, we did need approval for blended learning for these reasons:
1. Regardless of how school looks next year, some segment of our population will not attend school and will need remote learning.
2. We currently offer online learning in grades 6-12, and need to have this approval.
3. Finally, we may need remote learning for extended calamity days.
We will let you know what school will be like next year, as soon as we have some direction from the entities listed above.

post_text:
KIDS EAT FREE THIS SUMMER

Northwest Local would like to make sure that parents know the Ohio Department of Education is sponsoring the Summer Food Service Program again this summer, providing children through age 18 with free healthy meals when they lack access to school breakfasts and lunches. Children with disabilities and approved individualized education programs may take part through age 21.

It’s easy to participate in the Summer Food Service Program, and families do not need to sign up. Simply call 1-866-3-HUNGRY (1-866-348-6479), visit http://education.gov/kidsEat, or use the Department’s mobile app for meal times and locations. The Ohio Department of Education Mobile App (http://education.ohio.gov/App) is available for free in the Apple App Store and the Google Play Store, search Ohio Department of Education.

If you do not have one of the following devices in your home for your students to use to complete assigned online activities, please call (330) 854-7173 and leave a message including your name and a good contact number.
Devices for online learning include:
• Windows or Mac desktop computer
• Windows or Mac laptop computer
• Any brand of Chromebook
• iOS or Android tablet

post_text:
Northwest Middle School's Project Lead the Way is an engaging, hands-on classroom environment where students are empowered to use critical thinking skills to develop a knowledge base they need to thrive in the modern world.
Project Lead the Way sparks a joy of discovery and illuminates the range of paths students can look forward to in high school and beyond. Students apply knowledge and skills from a variety of disciplines.
Most recently, the students had to design a pull mechanism which would engage another gear and windmills that could harness the power of wind to complete a job near the ground.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?
v=NZ9AurNhVGU&feature=youtu.be

post_text:
Mrs. Szekely’s 1st Grade class has been very busy the 1st Quarter of the school year!

The class has watched monarch caterpillars transform into beautiful butterflies. They have taken in a performance of Peter and the Wolf performed by the Canton Ballet. Using Chromebooks and Google Classroom has been a new learning experience for them. Making 3D shapes with marshmallows and toothpicks was a “Yummy” Math day! Last, but definitely not least the students are loving becoming better READERS!!

The primary school started a new tradition this year. Every Friday is Spirit day for our school and each Friday the classes in the primary building participate in a spirit contest. The class wearing the most Indian Nation colors in gear win the presence of Spirit Bear and their room for the whole week!

This was our first win and we are so excited!

GO Tribe!
